cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the problem of stochastic online shortest path routing with end-to-end feedback, which is a natural application of the combinatorial stochastic bandits problem, a special case of the linear stochastic bandits problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
